{
  "displayName": "RinaWarp Terminal - Basic Monitoring Dashboard",
  "mosaicLayout": {
    "columns": 12,
    "tiles": [
      {
        "width": 6,
        "height": 4,
        "widget": {
          "title": "CPU Utilization",
          "scorecard": {
            "timeSeriesQuery": {
              "timeSeriesFilter": {
                "filter": "metric.type=\"compute.googleapis.com/instance/cpu/utilization\" resource.type=\"gce_instance\"",
                "aggregation": {
                  "alignmentPeriod": "60s",
                  "perSeriesAligner": "ALIGN_MEAN",
                  "crossSeriesReducer": "REDUCE_MEAN"
                }
              }
            },
            "sparkChartView": {
              "sparkChartType": "SPARK_LINE"
            }
          }
        }
      },
      {
        "xPos": 6,
        "width": 6,
        "height": 4,
        "widget": {
          "title": "Memory Usage",
          "scorecard": {
            "timeSeriesQuery": {
              "timeSeriesFilter": {
                "filter": "metric.type=\"agent.googleapis.com/memory/percent_used\" resource.type=\"gce_instance\"",
                "aggregation": {
                  "alignmentPeriod": "60s",
                  "perSeriesAligner": "ALIGN_MEAN",
                  "crossSeriesReducer": "REDUCE_MEAN"
                }
              }
            },
            "sparkChartView": {
              "sparkChartType": "SPARK_LINE"
            }
          }
        }
      },
      {
        "yPos": 4,
        "width": 12,
        "height": 4,
        "widget": {
          "title": "Network Traffic",
          "xyChart": {
            "dataSets": [
              {
                "timeSeriesQuery": {
                  "timeSeriesFilter": {
                    "filter": "metric.type=\"compute.googleapis.com/instance/network/received_bytes_count\" resource.type=\"gce_instance\"",
                    "aggregation": {
                      "alignmentPeriod": "60s",
                      "perSeriesAligner": "ALIGN_RATE",
                      "crossSeriesReducer": "REDUCE_SUM"
                    }
                  }
                },
                "plotType": "LINE",
                "targetAxis": "Y1"
              }
            ],
            "timeshiftDuration": "0s",
            "yAxis": {
              "label": "Bytes/sec",
              "scale": "LINEAR"
            }
          }
        }
      },
      {
        "yPos": 8,
        "width": 12,
        "height": 4,
        "widget": {
          "title": "RinaWarp Terminal Monitoring Overview",
          "text": {
            "content": "## RinaWarp Terminal Monitoring Dashboard\n\nThis dashboard provides basic monitoring for your RinaWarp Terminal application.\n\n### Current Metrics:\n- **CPU Utilization**: System processor usage\n- **Memory Usage**: RAM consumption (requires Ops Agent)\n- **Network Traffic**: Data transfer rates\n\n### Your Custom Metrics:\nBased on your application code, you can add custom metrics for:\n- Terminal Sessions (Active Connections)\n- API Request Rates\n- Error Rates\n- Response Times\n- AI Assistant Usage\n- Plugin Activity\n\n### Next Steps:\n1. Install the Ops Agent on your instances\n2. Set up custom metrics using the Google Cloud Monitoring API\n3. Configure alerting policies\n4. Create logs-based metrics\n\n[Learn more about Google Cloud Monitoring](https://cloud.google.com/monitoring)"
          }
        }
      }
    ]
  }
}
